# Fluff Date: 2026-03-04 21:00:04
<overview>
<p>The Cyrano (Plasma) is a variant developed by Paulina Weapons in 3071 specifically for the Taurian Defense Force. Leveraging light engine technology obtained through trade with the Outworlds Alliance, the design retains the exceptional speed of the base Cyrano while freeing enough tonnage to substantially improve armor protection and mount a plasma rifle better suited to escort duty against sophisticated modern threats. The Plasma variant was intended to address TDF commanders' longstanding frustration with the original Cyrano's thin protection and limited effectiveness against current armor, replacing the base model's large laser with a weapon traded to the Concordat specifically to help defend against the Davion threat on the Taurian frontier.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>The Cyrano (Plasma) employs a lighter fusion engine than the base model, made possible by technology shared with the Taurian Concordat through Outworlds Alliance trade. The engine swap retains the Cyrano's extraordinary speed while the saved tonnage is applied to two additional tons of Paulina DL ferro-fibrous armor, bringing total protection to a level commanders consider substantially more appropriate for an escort vehicle committed to contested airspace.</p><p>Primary armament is a plasma rifle from the Concordat's newer weapons inventory, replacing the Fuersturm-C large laser. The plasma rifle offers superior anti-armor penetration and a heat-inducing secondary effect that is especially useful for suppressing opposing aircraft and vehicles that rely on cooling efficiency. The Sky Tracer WL targeting system with Beagle Active Probe and Garret M250 communications carry forward from the base model unchanged, preserving the design's intelligence-gathering capabilities while adding dedicated strike-force firepower.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>The Cyrano (Plasma) serves the Taurian Defense Force as an escort gunship for Nightshade and Ripper heavy strike formations, replacing earlier model Cyranos in TDF air wings. Its plasma rifle armament makes it effective against armored opposition encountered during contested strike operations, and the additional armor improves crew survivability in engagements that exceed the standard Cyrano's narrow defensive margins. Deployment is concentrated in Taurian Concordat formations, with limited quantities allocated to allied militia organizations in the Hyades Rim. Despite persistent demand, the Protectorate Militia's transport and escort requirements routinely outpace available Plasma variant supply.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The Plasma variant's development is inseparable from the Taurian Concordat's security concerns in the early 3070s. Decades of Federated Suns pressure on the Taurian periphery had convinced TDF planners that the standard Cyrano's armament was insufficient against modern Davion air assets. The Outworlds Alliance's willingness to share plasma rifle technology as part of a broader diplomatic and trade arrangement gave Paulina engineers a weapon platform suited to address this requirement. Development proceeded concurrently with the New Vandenberg facility's reconstruction, and both the Plasma and ML variants entered production in late 3071.</p><p>The TDF's acceptance was immediate, and Protectorate Militia formations began transitioning from older Cyranos to the new model as production capacity allowed. The Blakist workers who staffed the rebuilt facility during its initial operational period provided technical continuity, though TDF and Paulina personnel moved steadily to assume full operational control over the following years.</p>
</history>

